{{Infobox person | name = Kjell Aamot | image = Kjell Aamot.jpg | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age |1950|9|7|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Trondheim]], Norway | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | monuments = | residence = | nationality = Norwegian | other_names = | education = | alma_mater = [[BI Norwegian Business School]] | occupation = businessperson | years_active = | employer = | organization = | agent = | known_for = | notable_works = | style = | influences = | influenced = | home_town = | television = | religion = | spouse = | partner = | children = | parents = | relatives = | awards = }} '''Kjell Aamot''' (born 7 November 1950) is a Norwegian business executive who chaired the [[Schibsted]] Media Group for twenty years.
Aamot is educated as economist from the [[BI Norwegian Business School]].<ref name=hvem>{{cite encyclopedia |encyclopedia= Hvem er hvem? |title=Aamot, Kjell |first=Anders |last=Bjartnes |authorlink= |editor-first=Knut Olav |editor-last=Åmås |year=2008 |editor-link=Knut Olav Åmås |publisher=Aschehoug |location=Oslo |ISBN=978-82-03-23561-0 |language=Norwegian |pages=655–656 }}</ref> He has had administrative position in [[Verdens Gang]], and served as CEO of [[Schibsted]] from 1989 to 2009.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Kjell Aamot |first= |last= |authorlink= |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |editor-last=Bolstad | editor-first=Erik | editor-link= |publisher=Norsk nettleksikon |location=Oslo |url=https://snl.no/Kjell_Aamot |language=Norwegian |accessdate=20 October 2018}}</ref>
