'''Sheraton Hotels and Resorts Hawaii''' is a [[Hawaii|Hawai{{okina}}i]] subsidiary of [[Starwood Hotels & Resorts Worldwide]] under the Sheraton brand name.  Based in [[Honolulu, Hawaii|Honolulu]], the corporate group administers and manages the five Sheraton Hotels and Resorts on the islands of [[Kauai|Kaua{{okina}}i]], [[Oahu|O{{okina}}ahu]], [[Maui]] and the [[Hawaii (island)|Big Island of Hawai{{okina}}i]]. The hotels and resorts in Waikīkī are the [[Sheraton Princess Kaiulani Hotel]] and the [[Sheraton Waikiki Hotel]]. Sheraton Kona Resort and Spa at [[Keauhou Bay]] is in [[Kona District, Hawaii|Kona]] on the Big Island while the [[Sheraton Maui]] is at [[Kaanapali Beach, Hawaii|Ka{{okina}}anapali Beach]].  The [[Sheraton Kauai Resort|Sheraton Kaua{{okina}}i Resort]] was renovated after being destroyed by [[Central Pacific Hurricane Center|Hurricane Iniki]] on September 11, 1992.
[[Image:Keauhou Bay.jpg|thumb|260px|Sheraton Kona Resort and Spa at [[Keauhou Bay]] includes the Kaleiopapa Convention Center]]


